    {
      "id": "sybil_9_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_9",
      "description": "Presenting a museum-grade 2004 BMW M3 (E46) that serves as a benchmark for longitudinal performance. This specimen is powered by the S54 3.2L inline-six, featuring six individual throttle bodies and a recalibrated Double VANOS system for optimal volumetric efficiency across the rev range. The powertrain is mated to a Getrag 6-speed manual transmission with a short-throw shifter and a heavy-duty Sachs clutch. The chassis has undergone comprehensive preventative maintenance, including structural subframe reinforcement and the installation of Bilstein B16 coilovers for dialed-in damping characteristics. Every suspension pick-up point remains factory-true, and the limited-slip M-differential provides exceptional torque vectoring. The exterior finish is flawless, exhibiting zero orange peel or clear coat failure, while the undercarriage is free of fluid weeping or oxidation. This is a turn-key collector-quality vehicle for the purist seeking peak mechanical harmony.",
      "price": 48900.0,
